[2026-01-17T15:21:36.089Z] Tool call read_file file=bmo://index.mjs reason=Confirm how AGENTS.md is inlined into the system prompt, especially with binaries and BMO_SOURCE.
bmo: Short answer
- When running the compiled binary from another directory, AGENTS.md is not inlined by default.
- bmo does not auto-read BMO_SOURCE/AGENTS.md for the system prompt.
- Use environment variables to opt in.

How to ensure AGENTS.md is inlined with the binary
- Inline the AGENTS.md that lives next to the installed tools (BMO_HOME):
  - export BMO_INLINE_NOTES=1
  This causes bmo to inline AGENTS.md located at BMO_HOME/AGENTS.md (the one we created).
- Inline a specific file (e.g., your source repo’s AGENTS.md):
  - export BMO_NOTES_FILE=/absolute/path/to/AGENTS.md
  This overrides and forces that file into the system prompt.

What BMO_SOURCE does
- BMO_SOURCE is used to mirror writes when creating/updating tools via bmo:// paths, so new tools persist back to your source repo.
- It is not used for reading AGENTS.md automatically.

Practical setups
- Use the AGENTS.md we installed with the binary:
  - export BMO_INLINE_NOTES=1
- Use your source repo’s AGENTS.md:
  - export BMO_NOTES_FILE=~/src/bmo-agent/AGENTS.md
- Disable notes entirely:
  - export BMO_DISABLE_NOTES=1

If you want, I can add a short “Notes behavior” section to AGENTS.md summarizing the above env vars so the behavior is self-documented.
